SIMPLE: engorgement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Engorgement
<hw>En*gorge"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>engorgement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of swallowing
greedily; a devouring with voracity; a glutting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An overfullness or obstruction of
the vessels in some part of the system; congestion.</def>
<rj><au>Hoblyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>The clogging of a blast
furnace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engouled</ent>⟦br⟧
